org.locationtech.geowave.mapreduce.input

Class InputFormatIteratorWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.mapreduce.input.InputFormatIteratorWrapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type for the entry
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Pair<GeoWaveInputKey,T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AsyncInputFormatIteratorWrapper

    public class InputFormatIteratorWrapper<T>
extends Object
implements Iterator<org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Pair<GeoWaveInputKey,T>>
    This is used internally to translate GeoWave rows into native objects (using the appropriate data adapter). It also performs any client-side filtering. It will peek at the next entry in the underlying datastore iterator to always maintain a reference to the next value.
